        "content": "<p>I just came across <strong>Display user statuses in the top navbar</strong> <a href=\"https://github.com/zulip/zulip/pull/15686\">#15686</a>. Should we add status icons to both the view label (as suggested in the issue) and message header bar for DM conversations?</p>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/b5/Ofq9bmsN6nnkxIDQY3NOIEgv/Screen-Shot-2023-06-05-at-9.24.52-PM.png\">Screen-Shot-2023-06-05-at-9.24.52-PM.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/b5/Ofq9bmsN6nnkxIDQY3NOIEgv/Screen-Shot-2023-06-05-at-9.24.52-PM.png\" title=\"Screen-Shot-2023-06-05-at-9.24.52-PM.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/b5/Ofq9bmsN6nnkxIDQY3NOIEgv/Screen-Shot-2023-06-05-at-9.24.52-PM.png\"></a></div><p>I think our general pattern is to display status icons everywhere in the main view (outside of settings) where the user's name is shown.</p>",
        "id": 1585928,
        "sender_full_name": "Alya Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1686025726
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/zulip/zulip/issues/15686#issuecomment-1578769874\">https://github.com/zulip/zulip/issues/15686#issuecomment-1578769874</a></p>",
